author: freep.com
title: Week 8 high school football roundup
text:
MORE Friday
Birmingham Groves 42, Royal Oak 0: Beau Kewley was 5-for-11 passing for 154 yards and two touchdowns for Groves. C.J. Boswell had 111 yards on 13 carries for one touchdown, and he had a 62 yard reception for a score. Earnest Allen had six carries for 52 yards and two touchdowns for Groves (8-0, 7-0). Royal Oak is 4-4, 4-3.
Clarkston 35, Lake Orion 14: Nolan Eriksen ran for 196 yards on 29 carries and three touchdowns for Clarkston (6-2. 6-1). Clarkston’s Kyle Genter blocked a punt and caught in the air and ran it in for a touchdown in the third quarter. Lake Orion is 3-4, 3-5.
Clinton Twp. Chippewa Valley 49, Macomb L’Anse Creuse North 14: Patrick Beriningstool was 22-for-31 passing for 262 and four touchdowns for Chippewa (6-1). Austin Childers had an interception return in the second quarter. Jalen Wells added with a pick six in the fourth quarter for Chippewa Valley.
Dearborn 28, Dearborn Fordson 14: Ali Berry ran for 55 yards and one touchdown on five carries for Dearborn (4-4). Michael Phillips was 11-for-19 passing for 120 yards and one touchdown. Dearborn Fordson is 5-3.
Dearborn Heights Crestwood 21, Garden City 13: Alah Salloum ran for 80 yards on six carries and one touchdown for Dearborn Crestwood (4-4). Hussein Fayz had eight carries for 54 yards. John Giangrande had 72 yards on 16 carries for Garden City (2-6).
Dearborn Heights Robichaud 58, Livonia Clarenceville 20: Jairus Grissom was 13-for-20 passing for 327 yards and five touchdown passes for Dearborn Robichaud (6-2). Traivon Clayton caught five passes for 113 yards, two touchdowns and a 70 yard punt return and a 50 yard interception return. Cortez Spears made 11 tackles, including one sack in the third. Livonia Clarenceville is 1-7.
Detroit Allen 18, Detroit Community 6: Shawn Steward was 6-for-10 for 105 yards and one touchdown for Allen Academy (5-3). Steward ran for 75 yards, including a 10 yard touchdown in the fourth quarter. Santangho Reynolds ran for 165 yards on 13 carries and one touchdown. Jason Williams had three catches for 75 yards, including a 48 yard score in the fourth quarter. Detroit Community is 1-7.
Farmington 44, Birmingham Seaholm 35: Kyle Brunson had 307 yards on 27 carries and three touchdowns for Farmington (5-3). Leigh Murray had two rushing touchdowns from 22 and 15 yards, and he threw a 32 yard touchdown pass for Birmingham (2-6).
Farmington Hills Harrison 35, North Farmington 0: Anthony Giovanni was 6-for-7 passing for 115 yards and one touchdown for Farmington Hills Harrison (7-1). Giovanni ran for 31 yards and one touchdown on four carries. Jamison Scarber made a 83-yard interception return for a touchdown.
Grosse Pointe South 28, Utica Ford 7: Logan Mico had two touchdowns for Grosse Pointe South (6-2, 3-2 MAC White). Sam Genna ran for 112 yards on 10 carries. Will Poplawski made nine tackles. Utica Ford is 5-3, 3-2.
Harper Woods 42, Hamtramck 26: Demone Roberson ran for 100 yards on 10 carries and two touchdowns for Harper Woods 5-3. Mike Moore had three carries for 23 yards and one touchdown. Dante Prim had five carries for 50 yards and two touchdowns. Hamtramck is 4-4.
Novi 35, Livonia Churchill 26: Emanuel Jackson compiled 228 total yards and four TDs, and Alec Bageris was 24-of-33 passing for 283 yards for Novi (4-4). Evan Cummins was 15-of-33 passing for 207 yards and three TDs for Churchill (4-4).
Riverview 21, Grosse Ile 20: Daniel Rice blocked an extra point at 04:38 left in the game. Shane Sparks ran for a 1-yard touchdown at 00:09 in the fourth quarter. Alex Hall ran for 168 yards and one touchdown on 34 carries. Tyler Chase had two touchdowns. Justin Moores was 14-for-30 passing for 250 yards and three touchdowns. Neil Smorch had three touchdowns.
Utica 27, Port Huron 20: Kumehnuu Gwilly rushed for 159 yards and three TDs on 20 carries for Utica (4-4). Patrick O’Connor was 9-of-15 passing for 153 yards and a TD pass to Slater Lutz.
Utica Eisenhower 30, Warren Mott 9: Max Wittwer was 8-for-15 passing for 98 yards and two touchdowns for Utica Eisenhower (5-3). Wittwer ran for one touchdown. Jack Provencher ran for 35 yards on four carries. John Stroble and Ryan Chargo each ran for a touchdown. Austin Mitchell had a 38-yard field goal.
Warren Cousino 35, Grosse Pointe North 34: Dan Maleszyk was 17-for-29 passing for 295 yards and three touchdown for Warren Cousino (5-3, 4-1). Cousino’s Karry DeBose ran for 134 yards on 23 carries and one touchdown. Jerrold King caught six passes for 182 yards and one touchdown. Warren Cousino won the MAC Blue Championship. Both teams will share the MAC Blue Championship.
Warren Fitzgerald 26, Clinton Twp. Clintondale 22: Stephen Gregerson was 12-for-24 passing for 162 yards for Warren Fitzgerald (6-5, 3-2 MAC Silver). Gregerson ran for 125 yards and four touchdowns on 21 carries. Delano Bolar made 12 tackles and a forced fumble.
Thursday
Detroit Western 45, Detroit Osborn 12: Western (2-6) quarterback K’Lari Sweeney went 11-17 for 243 yards and 4 touchdowns, and also had one rushing touchdown. Jaye Patrick and Brent Watson combined for 10 catches and five touchdowns. Kareem ray had 11 carries for 102 yards and one touchdown, also for Detroit Western. Osborn is 2-6.
